==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphocarbonic
<hw>Sul`pho*car*bon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a sulphacid,
<chform>H2CSO2</chform> (called also <altname>thiocarbonic</altname>
<it>acid</it>), or an acid, <chform>H2CS3</chform>, analogous to
carbonic acid, obtained as a yellow oily liquid of a pungent odor, and
forming salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphocyanate</ent>⟦br⟧
